7:
Am I gonna be fighting you,
Whitetail?
11:
No matter how many times I tell you
not to call me that... You're not
gonna listen, are you?
13:
Anyway, your opponent's him. Not
me.
27:
Ngh... No good, huh... Just a little bit
more, and I might've pulled it off.
38:
Lemme guess. You didn't go all out
because I'm your opponent.
40:
You're never gonna get stronger like
that.
49: Did it look like I wasn't trying?
53:
Perhaps he sensed your lack of
hostility and believed you weren't
truly willing to fight him.
58:
...Well, I definitely wanna give him a
good smack whenever he gives me
attitude, at least.
66:
You know, I wanted to see what
fighting with martial arts was like, so
I sparred with Nimbus.
73:
I was awful. I think even if I seriously
fought him with my sword, he'd still
beat me.
75:
And you know what? In this town,
there are plenty of others that are
even stronger than him.
78:
Light even implied that he could
beat Nimbus if he was still in his
prime.
85:
I'm not the type of person that can
beat someone around my skill level
by trying to throw them off their
game.
89:
Also, I'm gonna win next time. Don't
care how fast you are, I'll get you.
93:
Huh. Didn't expect that much
attitude from you.
97:
Well, I've learned a thing or two
about throwing shade from a
certain someone here.
103:
But you know what? If you wanna
get your butt kicked so bad, I'll be
happy to do it.
106:
Oh yeah? You're just fast. Once I get
used to your speed, you're done for.
116:
Just outta curiosity... Why are you so
obsessed with getting stronger?
121:
...Even though I can never be the
strongest? Because I'm one of the
rabbitfolk? Is that what you're
getting at?
123:
Okay, yeah, maybe you and me...
We're far from the top.
128:
If someone looks down on me, then
I'm a hundred percent gonna get
stronger than them. Doesn't matter
who.
131:
Doesn't matter how big. Bigger they
are, harder they fall.
134:
That's how I'll become the strongest
out there.
139:
Wow... I mean, I don't get where
you're coming from, but... Your big
talk made me feel a little something.
142:
Heh. You wanna get your face
pummeled that badly?
146:
You know, I'm under no delusion I'll
ever be the strongest out there.
Don't feel like I need to be either.
150:
But I definitely will beat you. When I
do, will that make me the best
fighter in existence?
153:
...That's the stupidest thing I've ever
heard.
157:
But I can deal with stupid. Whatever
challenge comes my way, I'll beat it.
159: I'll get stronger no matter what!
